%N A339942 Triangle read by rows: T(n,k) is the number of permutations of the cyclic group Z/nZ whose longest embedded arithmetic progression has length k.
%C A339942 For the case k=2, it can be proved that if n is a power of 2, then T(n,2)=2^{n-1}; otherwise T(n,2)=0 (Lemma 8 of Goh and Zhao (2020)). It can also be shown that T(n,n) = n*phi(n), where phi is the Euler totient function.
%H A339942 M. K. Goh and R. Y. Zhao, <a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2012.12339">Arithmetic subsequences in a random ordering of an additive set</a>, arXiv:2012.12339 [math.CO], 2020.
%F A339942 T(n,n) = n*A000010(n).
